news.title: Unemployment benefits reduce risk of food insecurity
news.summary: A 2020 study on government benefits and food insecurity during the coronavirus crisis has found that the $600 per week federal unemployment insurance was linked to a 4.4 percentage point reduction in food insecurity.

news.title: Unemployment exacerbates food insecurity
news.summary: Around 31% of households earning less than $75,000 who experienced unemployment at any point during the pandemic became food insecure, according to a July 2020 study from the National Center for Biotechnology Information (NCBI).
